<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="52" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,152,1724]" pageId="3" pageNumber="52">
<bibRefCitation author="Herzog, T." box="[198,370,1273,1299]" pageId="3" pageNumber="52" pagination="82 - 88" refId="ref5072" refString="Herzog, T. (1924) Neue Sudamerikanische Eriocaulonaceae. Repertorium Specierum Novarum Regni Vegetabilis 20: 82 - 88." type="journal article" year="1924">Herzog (1924)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName box="[498,667,1273,1298]" class="Liliopsida" family="Eriocaulaceae" genus="Paepalanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="3" pageNumber="52" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="chiquitensis">
<emphasis box="[498,667,1273,1298]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="52">P. chiquitensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
on the basis of field observations, but he stated in the protologue that only fragments (parts of an inflorescence, 
<emphasis box="[740,882,1312,1337]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="52">Herzog 114</emphasis>
) is the 
<typeStatus box="[979,1087,1312,1338]" pageId="3" pageNumber="52">holotype</typeStatus>
at 
<collectionCode box="[1128,1150,1312,1338]" country="Netherlands" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15678" name="Nationaal Herbarium Nederland, Leiden University branch" pageId="3" pageNumber="52" type="Herbarium">L</collectionCode>
. However, the original description and 
<typeStatus box="[343,394,1350,1376]" pageId="3" pageNumber="52">type</typeStatus>
specimen are insufficient to distinguish the species unambiguously without additional evidence. Thus, on the basis of article 9.7 of the ICBN (
<bibRefCitation author="McNeill, J. &amp; Barrie, F. R. &amp; Burdet, H. M. &amp; Demoulin, V. &amp; Hawksworth, D. L. &amp; Markhold, K. &amp; Nicolson, D. H. &amp; Prado, J. &amp; Silva, J. P. C. &amp; Skog, J. E. &amp; Wiersema, J. H. &amp; Turland, N. J." box="[805,1041,1389,1415]" pageId="3" pageNumber="52" refId="ref5205" refString="McNeill, J., Barrie, F. R., Burdet, H. M., Demoulin, V., Hawksworth, D. L., Markhold, K., Nicolson, D. H., Prado, J., Silva, J. P. C., Skog, J. E., Wiersema, J. H. &amp; Turland, N. J. (eds.) (2006) International Code of Botanical Nomenclature. Guntner Verlag. Ruggell, 568 pp." type="book" year="2006">
McNeill 
<emphasis box="[912,970,1389,1414]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="52">et al.</emphasis>
2006
</bibRefCitation>
), we hereby designate an epitype. 
<taxonomicName box="[151,473,1428,1453]" class="Liliopsida" family="Eriocaulaceae" genus="Paepalanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="3" pageNumber="52" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="chiquitensis">
<emphasis box="[151,473,1428,1453]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="52">Paepalanthus chiquitensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the most widespread and variable species in section 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ruhland" authorityYear="1903" box="[1156,1309,1428,1453]" class="Liliopsida" family="Eriocaulaceae" genus="Paepalanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="3" pageNumber="52" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Diphyomene">
<emphasis box="[1156,1309,1428,1453]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="52">Diphyomene</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, therefore several formerly described species are treated here as synonyms.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,152,1724]" pageId="3" pageNumber="52">
<bibRefCitation author="Sano, P. T." box="[198,348,1505,1531]" pageId="3" pageNumber="52" pagination="99 - 107" refId="ref5604" refString="Sano, P. T. (2004) Actinocephalus (Korn.) Sano (Paepalanthus sect. Actinocephalus), a new genus of Eriocaulaceae, and other taxonomic and nomenclatural changes involving Paepalanthus Mart. Taxon 53 (1): 99 - 107." type="journal article" year="2004">Sano (2004)</bibRefCitation>
proposed 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sano" authorityYear="2004" box="[481,769,1505,1530]" class="Liliopsida" family="Eriocaulaceae" genus="Paepalanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="3" pageNumber="52" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="giganteus">
<emphasis box="[481,769,1505,1530]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="52">Paepalanthus giganteus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a new name for the later homonym 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Martius" authorityYear="1834" box="[1275,1436,1505,1530]" class="Liliopsida" family="Eriocaulaceae" genus="Paepalanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="3" pageNumber="52" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1275,1436,1505,1530]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="52">Paepalanthus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicName authority="(Bong.) Koern. In" authorityName="Koern. Finally, Trovo &amp; Sano" authorityYear="2010" baseAuthorityName="Bong." box="[151,490,1544,1570]" class="Liliopsida" family="Eriocaulaceae" genus="Paepalanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="3" pageNumber="52" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="speciosus">
<emphasis box="[151,266,1544,1569]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="52">speciosus</emphasis>
(Bong.) Koern. In
</taxonomicName>
the protologue, 
<bibRefCitation author="Sano, P. T." box="[690,837,1544,1570]" pageId="3" pageNumber="52" pagination="99 - 107" refId="ref5604" refString="Sano, P. T. (2004) Actinocephalus (Korn.) Sano (Paepalanthus sect. Actinocephalus), a new genus of Eriocaulaceae, and other taxonomic and nomenclatural changes involving Paepalanthus Mart. Taxon 53 (1): 99 - 107." type="journal article" year="2004">Sano (2004)</bibRefCitation>
indicated the collection 
<emphasis box="[1136,1280,1544,1569]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="52">
Riedel 
<quantity box="[1221,1280,1544,1569]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.842" pageId="3" pageNumber="52" unit="in" value="2300.0">2300</quantity>
</emphasis>
in LE as the 
<typeStatus box="[151,254,1582,1608]" pageId="3" pageNumber="52">holotype</typeStatus>
of the basionym. However, this material was collected 4 years after the species publication and thus cannot be the 
<typeStatus box="[314,420,1621,1647]" pageId="3" pageNumber="52">holotype</typeStatus>
. As Bongard (1831) did not clearly indicate a type specimen and no original collection belonging to the same species has been found in LE, we consider the original material lost and designate the specimen cited by 
<bibRefCitation author="Sano, P. T." box="[370,513,1698,1724]" pageId="3" pageNumber="52" pagination="99 - 107" refId="ref5604" refString="Sano, P. T. (2004) Actinocephalus (Korn.) Sano (Paepalanthus sect. Actinocephalus), a new genus of Eriocaulaceae, and other taxonomic and nomenclatural changes involving Paepalanthus Mart. Taxon 53 (1): 99 - 107." type="journal article" year="2004">Sano (2004)</bibRefCitation>
as a 
<typeStatus box="[573,666,1698,1724]" pageId="3" pageNumber="52">neotype</typeStatus>
for the species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
